summary: I get why Chloe is angry and hurt and striking out. She didn’t deserve to be used and treated the way that Lucas did. She’s...
body:
I get why Chloe is angry and hurt and striking out. She didn’t deserve to be used and treated the way that Lucas did. She’s human and a teenage girl who was used as a beard, made to believe things, and was then ghosted. I get why she did what she did.

But it’s still not ok to out someone like that and the way she did it.

Lucas’s sexuality is his own private business and yes he did use her for a shield, but it wasn’t used in a with cruelty in mind. He’s scared, confused, and ashamed, he doesn’t want to be gay. He wants to be normal or at least what he thinks normal is.

Outing him without his consent or said with harmful intent. She wanted him to suffer and it wasn’t her secret to tell.
